 situates the book in the context of developments in current scholarship and the epilogue discusses the effects of recent economic and political changes in the American labor movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aClass consciousnesszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aLabor unionszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWorking classzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Minority Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822381730zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822381730423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822381730.jpg  a978-3-11-071360-2  DUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles